    "faq_W8bJFX": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "item_fPVkXg": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the difference between the Telescopic High Window Cleaner and the High Reach Van Cleaner?",
            "content": "<p>Both window cleaners feature the same cleaning head. The Telescopic High Window Cleaner comes with a telescopic handle, whereas the High Reach Van Cleaner is sold as the cleaning head only and attaches to the 4-part-handle sold that comes with the Caravan Cleaning Bundle.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_egcamj": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I know which window cleaner to choose?",
            "content": "<p>The best window cleaner for you depends on the type of windows you’re looking to clean.</p><p>Our <strong>Glider Magnetic Window Cleaners</strong> are ideal for cleaning both sides of your windows at the same time, where you have access to place the exterior cleaning pad.</p><p>Our <strong>Telescopic High Window Cleaner</strong> is designed for high and hard-to-reach windows, allowing you to clean safely from the ground.</p><p>For smaller, easily accessible areas, our <strong>Mini Mop</strong> is a versatile option that can be used by hand to clean windows and a variety of other surfaces around your home.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_DTBx6Q": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How high can the Telescopic High Window Cleaner reach?",
            "content": "<p>The adjustable telescopic handle extends your reach, making it ideal for cleaning high windows, skylights, solar panels, awnings, glass doors and other hard-to-reach areas without the need for ladders. Fully extended, the handle itself is 177cm long.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_FfLXTg": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What surfaces can I use the BrightTools range of window cleaners on?",
            "content": "<p>Our range of window cleaners are suitable for a variety of smooth surfaces including glass windows, mirrors, shower screens and glass doors. They are perfect for removing fingerprints, water marks, dust and everyday grime.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_3bNTBW": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I use the High Reach Window Cleaner without a ladder?",
            "content": "<p>Yes! The telescopic handle is designed to help you clean high and hard-to-reach windows safely from the ground, making window cleaning easier, quicker and more convenient.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_FKDVgG": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How to clean high rise windows from inside?",
            "content": "<p>The best way to clean high rise windows from inside is with our Telescopic High Window Cleaner. Use the microfibre pad first to scrub with water and soap, and then use the squeegee side to remove the excess water for a streak-free finish.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_PWrdrT": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do you clean the outside of windows without having access?",
            "content": "<p>Our Glider range of Magnetic Window Cleaners allows you to clean both sides of your windows at the same time. Simply place the exterior cleaning part on the outside of the window (where accessible) and the magnetic design keeps both sides connected for an effortless clean.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_CGMC84": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do you clean high windows without a ladder?",
            "content": "<p>You can clean high windows without a ladder using a high window cleaner (with a telescopic handle) or magnetic window cleaner for windows that there is no access to the outer part of the windows.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_yktDVD": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do you get streak free windows?",
            "content": "<p>In order to get streak free windows you have to use a high-quality window cleaner, wash the window with water and soap, use the squeegee side to remove excess water, and then dry the windows with a microfibre pad to remove any streaks.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_zjjzkE": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What to use to clean high windows?",
            "content": "<p>Cleaning hard-to-reach windows is now easier with our High Reach Window Cleaner. Featuring a telescopic handle, microfibre cloth and squeegee, it allows you to wash, wipe and dry your windows from the safety of the ground. Simply scrub with the microfibre cloth, then remove water and streaks with the squeegee for a crystal-clear finish.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
